#* {{quote-book|author=Shirley Geok-lin Lim|authorlink=Shirley Geok-lin Lim|chapter=8|title=Joss and Gold|location=Singapore|publisher=[[w:Marshall Cavendish|Marshall Cavendish Editions]]|year=2010|page=254|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=pSKJAAAAQBAJ&pg=PA254|isbn=978-981-4302-11-1|passage=Suyin recognized him immediately—the tall, uncomfortable-looking white man, the '''''ang moh''''' standing guard by the only unoccupied table in the cafe.}}
#* {{quote-journal|author=Wong Wei Han|quotee=Stephen Krempl|title=One bold move catapulted him to global stage: Man who heads his own HR consulting firm believes his willingness to stand out from the crowd and be counted was key to his success|url=http://www.straitstimes.com/business/one-bold-move-catapulted-him-to-global-stage|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150901212302/http://www.straitstimes.com/business/one-bold-move-catapulted-him-to-global-stage|archivedate=1 September 2015|newspaper={{w|The Straits Times}}|location=Singapore|date=1 August 2015|passage=With my kind of career and background, I have the best of both worlds. You can't tell me I'm that '''ang moh''' (Caucasian) who doesn't understand. I'm the Asian who's been through the same challenges, and I would show you how to overcome them.}}

